Create a class Product with following attributes:
no, name, price, stock
then create a constructor (initializer)
a method getDiscount which returns the discount as follows:
10% if the price is 100+
5% if the price is 70+
and zero if less than 70

a method to receive a required quantity and check if sufficient stock, so it return true or false

a method to print out all details of product 

in the main:
create an array of products and let the user enter the data, then let the user enter a product name check if its found as the user to enter the required quantity and check if the stock is sufficient then calculate the total of this product with discount.
Let the user be able to buy as many products as they want and find the grand total and print it out at the end